To install:

you can use your own mongoDB server or install docker and run mongoDb on docker.

You can use this link for moongoDb:
https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/setup-mongodb-docker-linux-container-windows-10-volume-kumaran/

URIlink for mongoDB: mongodb://admin:p@ssword@localhost:27017/?authMechanism=DEFAULT&authSource=admin

After installing these open project folder and run:

npm install

This command line will install all requirements.

You can import csv files through MongoDB Compass.

After succesful installation run this command to run app:
nodemon app

You should see "connected to db" sentence. This means you succesfully connected to database and can work on a project